definition: that/those/then (in that case)/commonly pr. [nei4] before a classifier, esp. in Beijing

sentences.english: There are many coyotes in Arizona.
sentences.chinese: 在亞利桑那有許多郊狼。

sentences.english: In Arizona, I have had plenty of distraction from the running.
sentences.chinese: 在亞利桑那，有很多事情能讓我從跑步中分散注意力。

sentences.english: Arizona timber tree with bluish silvery foliage.
sentences.chinese: 亞利桑那木材，葉帶藍色，有。

sentences.english: Now I see some cactuses out in Arizona.
sentences.chinese: 現在我看到了亞利桑那的仙人掌。

sentences.english: Why had this hard-living Arizona boy embraced Islam?
sentences.chinese: 這位生活艱難的亞利桑那男孩爲什麼皈依伊斯蘭教？

sentences.english: In Arizona, I still have some freedoms.
sentences.chinese: 在亞利桑那，我還有點自由。

sentences.english: Mine' s in Arizona, Julio says and spits into the street.
sentences.chinese: 我是在亞利桑那，胡利歐說，吐到街上。

sentences.english: I remember when we just go into California from Arizona to pick up the carrot harvest.
sentences.chinese: 我記得我們剛剛從亞利桑那到加利福尼亞去收胡蘿蔔。

sentences.english: A bumblebee draws nectar from an Arizona sunflower.
sentences.chinese: 一隻大黃蜂正在一株亞利桑那向日葵上吸取花蜜。
